---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: The Civil Rights Movement — How They Won
description: The Civil Rights Movement was not a moral awakening. It was a disciplined political campaign that used economic disruption, legal challenges, and civil disobedience to make segregation too costly to sustain. They won the Civil Rights Act and the Voting Rights Act — and the vote that passed both proves why the parties switched.
permalink: /civil-rights/
---

<section class="hero hero--short" id="chapter-intro" data-chapter="Civil Rights">
  <div class="hero__content">
    <span class="eyebrow">1954 – 1968</span>
